SUMMARY:Youth Clowning with Mick Holsbeke
DESCRIPTION:Unleash your silly side! A playful\, youth-friendly class using improv\, physical comedy\, and clown games to build confidence & creativity\n\n\n\nGet ready to unleash your silly side! This series is all about having fun\, taking creative risks\, and finding the funny in the unexpected. Working as a group to start\, participants will dive head-over-heels into ensemble theater\, improvisation\, physical comedy\, and clown-inspired games\, learning how to turn everyday moments into laugh-out-loud comedy. Whether you’re interested in performing or just want to break out of your comfort zone\, this session is all about embracing play\, thinking on your feet\, and making bold comedic choices. No experience? No problem! Just bring your imagination\, a sense of humor\, and a willingness to get ridiculous. \nClass Details\nDates: Six (6) Monday classes \nTime: 4:00 pm to 5:20 pm \nLocation: The Clown Garage at Improv School Eastside Issaquah \n1315 NW Mall Street\, Suite 4 Issaquah\, WA 98027 (next to the Gaslamp Bar & Grill) \nMaximum students: 12 \nAges: 10-15 \nCost: $270 \nPrerequisite: None
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/youth-clowning-with-mick-holsbeke/
LOCATION:Clown Garage at the Improv School Issaquah\, 1315 NW Mall Street\, Suite 4\, Issaquah\, WA\, 98027
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Youth-Clowning-1.png
END:VEVENT
