SUMMARY:Clown 100: The Foundations of Clown Play with Mick Holsbeke
DESCRIPTION:Step into the playful world of Clown! Explore presence\, vulnerability\, and joyful failure through ensemble play and laughter\n\n\n\nWelcome to the world of clowning! This foundational class invites you to step into the playful\, unpredictable\, and joy-filled realm of Clowning with other folks. Through a series of dynamic exercises in presence\, play\, rhythm\, tension\, emotional expression\, and ensemble play\, participants will explore what makes Clown so hilarious and contagious. Embracing vulnerability and the fine art of making mistakes\, we’ll turn failure into laughter and endless comic gold. Whether you’re new to performance or a seasoned artist\, this series will help you build confidence\, take creative risks\, and refine your Clown instincts. Come ready to play\, surprise yourself\, and find the fun in the unexpected! \nClass Details\nDates: Six (6) Mondays classes \nTime: 7:00 pm to 8:30 pm \nLocation: The Clown Garage at Improv School Eastside Issaquah \n1315 NW Mall Street\, Suite 4 Issaquah\, WA 98027 (next to the Gaslamp Bar & Grill) \nMaximum students: 16 \nAges: 18 plus \nCost: $270 \nPrerequisite: None
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/clown-100-the-foundations-of-clown-play-with-mick-holsbeke-2/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike Place Market\, Seattle\, WA\, 98101\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Clown-100.png
END:VEVENT
